Reasoning: The paper discusses a learning approach for mobile robot navigation, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of an Artificial Immune System (AIS) and Genetic Algorithm (GA) suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY). The comparison with a hand-designed controller and the testing of the idiotypic mechanism being turned off suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE).
